Join us in Todos Santos!

Please join us for our computational biology workshop at the CSU Center in Todos Santos, Mexico. Here is a summary of the topics that we are looking forward to covering over the course of the week.



Workshop registration is open! Please register by February 28, 2023 (although we encourage any interested participants to still inquire about availability even if it is past that date).

Computational Workshop

Instructors: Kim Hoke, Tai Montgomery, Dan Sloan, Mark Stenglein

Monday April 24: Introduction to high-throughput sequencing, computational biology, and code management

  • 09:00-09:30 Arrival and Check-In
  • 09:30-10:30 Introduction to Todos Santos and Group Discussion
  • 10:30-12:00 High-Throughput Sequencing Technologies
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:30 UNIX and Command Line Tools (part I)
  • 14:30-16:00 UNIX and Command Line Tools (part II)
  • 16:00-17:00 Workflow Manangement (Snakemake)

Tuesday April 25: RNA-seq

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-12:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis I
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis II

Wednesday April 26: Genomic analysis I

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Introduction to Genomic Analysis
  • 10:00-12:00 Manipulating and Obtaining Genomics Data
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-15:00 Alignment and Read Mapping
  • 15:00-18:00 Workshop social and research presentations

Thursday April 27: Genomic analysis II

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-12:00 Assembly and Annotation
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-16:00 Variant Calling

Friday April 28: Data Visualization

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Code Management (GitHub)
  • 10:00-10:30 Introduction to R, R Markdown, and Data Visualization
  • 10:30-12:00 Plotting Genomic Data with R and ggplot
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:00 Figure Drawing in R
  • 14:00-15:00 Circular Representations of Genomic Data with Circos
  • 15:00-16:00 Local BLAST and Comparative Genomics
  • 16:00 End of workshop
